<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="172" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="11.[148,1356,1251,2108]" pageId="11" pageNumber="172">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[149,505,1838,1871]" pageId="11" pageNumber="172">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Endangered on The IUCN Red List. The Dark Shrew 
<taxonomicName box="[243,339,1877,1910]" class="Mammalia" family="Tenrecidae" genus="Tenrec" kingdom="Animalia" order="Afrosoricida" pageId="11" pageNumber="172" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Tenrec</taxonomicName>
is known from two broadly disjunct populations in northern and eastern Madagascar, with area of occupancy of only 282 km? Population trends are unknown. [tis threatened by habitat loss and degradation including human disturbance offorest and mining activities.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
